**Task:** Add a new button using the shared Button design system.

**Design rules**
- Font: Inter, normal weight (no bold)
- Corners: rounded-2xl
- Motion: transition-all duration-200
- Focus state: focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-600/40
- Disabled: opacity-50 and no pointer events
- Icons: optional, 16‚Äì20px, spaced with gap-2

**Variants**
- Primary: bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700 active:scale-[0.98]
- Secondary: bg-white text-gray-900 border border-gray-200 hover:bg-gray-50
- Ghost: bg-transparent text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-100
- Danger: bg-red-600 text-white hover:bg-red-700

**Sizes**
- sm: h-9 px-3 text-sm
- md (default): h-10 px-4 text-base
- lg: h-12 px-6 text-lg

**Code (Button component)**
```tsx
import React from "react";
type ButtonProps = React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> & {
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "ghost" | "danger";
  size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
  full?: boolean;
  leftIcon?: React.ReactNode;
  rightIcon?: React.ReactNode;
};

export function Button({
  variant = "primary",
  size = "md",
  full = false,
  leftIcon,
  rightIcon,
  className = "",
  children,
  ...props
}: ButtonProps) {
  const base =
    "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-2xl transition-all duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-600/40 disabled:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none gap-2";
  const sizes = {
    sm: "h-9 px-3 text-sm",
    md: "h-10 px-4 text-base",
    lg: "h-12 px-6 text-lg",
  }[size];
  const variants = {
    primary: "bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700 active:scale-[0.98]",
    secondary:
      "bg-white text-gray-900 border border-gray-200 hover:bg-gray-50",
    ghost: "bg-transparent text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-100",
    danger: "bg-red-600 text-white hover:bg-red-700",
  }[variant];

  return (
    <button
      className={`${base} ${sizes} ${variants} ${full ? "w-full" : ""} ${className}`}
      {...props}
    >
      {leftIcon}
      {children}
      {rightIcon}
    </button>
  );
}

## ü™ü Cursor Block: **Add a New Window**

```md
**Task:** Add a new window component. Use WindowCard for on-page panels and Modal for overlays. Both share the same design.

**Shared design rules**
- Background: bg-white
- Border: border border-gray-200
- Corners: rounded-2xl
- Shadow: shadow-lg
- Padding: p-6 md:p-8
- Typography: Inter, no bold
- Layout: Header ‚Üí Body ‚Üí (optional) Actions
- Actions: mt-6 flex items-center gap-3 justify-end

---

### A) WindowCard (on-page panel)
```tsx
type WindowCardProps = {
  title?: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  actions?: React.ReactNode;
  className?: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
};

export function WindowCard({ title, subtitle, actions, className = "", children }: WindowCardProps) {
  return (
    <section className={`bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 md:p-8 ${className}`}>
      {(title || subtitle) && (
        <header className="mb-4">
          {title && <h2 className="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-900 leading-tight">{title}</h2>}
          {subtitle && <p className="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">{subtitle}</p>}
        </header>
      )}
      <div>{children}</div>
      {actions && <div className="mt-6 flex items-center gap-3 justify-end">{actions}</div>}
    </section>
  );
}

